# Banking deep map

## Flow

UI `banking/` → `banking.service.ts` → `/api/banking/*` → `routes/banking.js` → `db/banking.js` (+ `banking-advanced.js`). Statement upload → `parseBankStatement` → fingerprint dedupe → `importTransactions`.

## Parsers (`utils/bank-parsers/`)

| File | Bank |
|------|------|
| `hdfc-csv.js` | HDFC CSV |
| `icici-xls.js` | ICICI Excel |
| `dcb-xls.js` | DCB Excel |
| `sbi.js` | SBI |
| `axis.js` | Axis |
| `kotak.js` | Kotak |
| `cotak-csv.js` | Kotak CSV variant |
| `generic.js` | Fallback CSV/XLS |
| `common.js` | `finalizeParsedTxn`, shared categorize |
| `index.js` | detect order + PDF reject |

Hints: `bankHint` HDFC|ICICI|DCB|SBI|AXIS|KOTAK. Custom rules re-applied after parse.

## Data

- Account: bank_name, account_name, account_number, ifsc, account_type, currency, opening_balance.
- Txn: txn_date, narration, ref_no, withdrawal/deposit, balance, category, category_source, payee, fingerprint, import_batch_id, linked_transfer_id.
- Rules: pattern, match_field (default narration), category, priority, optional account_id.
- Budgets: category, amount, period_month `YYYY-MM`.

## Advanced (`banking-advanced.js`)

Category rules CRUD, bulk delete, undo import batch, manual create txn, balance continuity, budgets/status, recurring detection, transfer matching (windowDays), cash forecast.

## FE service methods

Accounts/txns CRUD, bulk categorize, analytics, categories, rules, budget status, recurring, forecast, continuity — mirror route names in `banking.service.ts`.
